@startuml
title Conway's Law: Org Structure Mirrors Architecture

skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor White
  BorderColor Black
}
skinparam arrow {
  Color Black
}

rectangle "Organization" as ORG  #ffffaa {
  rectangle "Team A" as TeamA
  rectangle "Team B" as TeamB
  rectangle "Team C" as TeamC
}

rectangle "System Architecture" as SYS #ffaa88 {
  rectangle "Service A" as ServiceA
  rectangle "Service B" as ServiceB
  rectangle "Service C" as ServiceC
}

TeamA -down-> ServiceA : communication\ninfluences design
TeamB -down-> ServiceB
TeamC -down-> ServiceC

note top of ORG
  Communication paths and
  team boundaries on the left...
end note

note bottom of SYS
  ...tend to show up as
  system boundaries on the right.
end note
@enduml